        "digitizedText": "## 3.2 Polynomial Division\nWhen dividing a polynomial $P(x)$ by a linear divisor $(x - c)$, the result can be written as:\n$$P(x) = (x - c)Q(x) + R$$\nwhere $Q(x)$ is the quotient and $R$ is the constant remainder.\n\nIf the divisor is in the form $(ax - b)$, the relationship is:\n$$P(x) = (ax - b)Q(x) + R$$",
