        "digitizedText": "## 3.4 The Factor Theorem\nThe Factor Theorem is a special case of the Remainder Theorem. It states that if $P(c) = 0$, then $(x - c)$ is a factor of the polynomial $P(x)$. Conversely, if $(x - c)$ is a factor of $P(x)$, then $P(c) = 0$.\n\nFor a linear divisor $(ax - b)$, $(ax - b)$ is a factor if and only if $P\\left(\\frac{b}{a}\\right) = 0$.",
